Dimensions.Name: Ad Content
Dimensions.Description: When using manual campaign tracking, the value of the utm_content campaign tracking parameter. When using AdWords autotagging, the first line of the text for your online Ad campaign. If you are using mad libs for your AdWords content, this field displays the keywords you provided for the mad libs keyword match. Otherwise the value is (not set)

Dimensions.Name: Ad Distribution Network
Dimensions.Description: The networks used to deliver your ads (Content, Search, Search partners, etc.).

Dimensions.Name: Ad Format
Dimensions.Description: Your AdWords ad formats (Text, Image, Flash, Video, etc.).

Dimensions.Name: Ad Group
Dimensions.Description: The name of your AdWords ad group.

Dimensions.Name: Ad Slot
Dimensions.Description: The location of the advertisement on the hosting page (Top, RHS, or not set).

Dimensions.Name: Ad Slot Position
Dimensions.Description: The ad slot positions in which your AdWords ads appeared (1-8).

Dimensions.Name: AdWords Ad Group ID
Dimensions.Description: A string. Corresponds to AdWords API AdGroup.id.

Dimensions.Name: AdWords Campaign ID
Dimensions.Description: A string. Corresponds to AdWords API Campaign.id.

Dimensions.Name: AdWords Creative ID
Dimensions.Description: A string. Corresponds to AdWords API Ad.id.

Dimensions.Name: AdWords Criteria ID
Dimensions.Description: A string. Corresponds to AdWords API Criterion.id.

Dimensions.Name: AdWords Customer ID
Dimensions.Description: A string. Corresponds to AdWords API AccountInfo.customerId.

Dimensions.Name: Affiliation
Dimensions.Description: Typically used to designate a supplying company or brick and mortar location; product affiliation.

Dimensions.Name: Affinity Category (reach)
Dimensions.Description: Indicates that users are more likely to be interested in learning about the specified category.

Dimensions.Name: Age
Dimensions.Description: Age bracket of user.

Dimensions.Name: App ID
Dimensions.Description: The ID of the application.

Dimensions.Name: App Installer ID
Dimensions.Description: ID of the installer (e.g., Google Play Store) from which the app was downloaded. By default, the app installer id is set based on the PackageManager#getInstallerPackageName method.

Dimensions.Name: App Name
Dimensions.Description: The name of the application.

Dimensions.Name: App Version
Dimensions.Description: The version of the application.

Dimensions.Name: Browser
Dimensions.Description: The names of browsers used by users to your website. For example, Internet Explorer or Firefox.

Dimensions.Name: Browser Version
Dimensions.Description: The browser versions used by users to your website. For example, 2.0.0.14

Dimensions.Name: Campaign
Dimensions.Description: When using manual campaign tracking, the value of the utm_campaign campaign tracking parameter. When using AdWords autotagging, the name(s) of the online ad campaign that you use for your property. Otherwise the value (not set) is used.

Dimensions.Name: Checkout Options
Dimensions.Description: User options specified during the checkout process, e.g., FedEx, DHL, UPS for delivery options or Visa, MasterCard, AmEx for payment options. This dimension should be used along with ga:shoppingStage (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: City
Dimensions.Description: The cities of property users, derived from IP addresses.

Dimensions.Name: Continent
Dimensions.Description: The continents of property users, derived from IP addresses.

Dimensions.Name: Correlation Model ID
Dimensions.Description: Correlation Model ID for related products.

Dimensions.Name: Count of Sessions
Dimensions.Description: The session index for a user to your property. Each session from a unique user will get its own incremental index starting from 1 for the first session. Subsequent sessions do not change previous session indicies. For example, if a certain user has 4 sessions to your website, sessionCount for that user will have 4 distinct values of '1' through '4'.

Dimensions.Name: Country / Territory
Dimensions.Description: The country of users, derived from IP addresses.

Dimensions.Name: Currency Code
Dimensions.Description: The local currency code of the transaction based on ISO 4217 standard.

Dimensions.Name: Custom Dimension XX
Dimensions.Description: The name of the requested custom dimension, where XX refers the number/index of the custom dimension.

Dimensions.Name: Custom Variable (Key XX)
Dimensions.Description: The name for the requested custom variable.

Dimensions.Name: Custom Variable (Value XX)
Dimensions.Description: The value for the requested custom variable.

Dimensions.Name: Date
Dimensions.Description: The date of the session formatted as YYYYMMDD.

Dimensions.Name: Day Index
Dimensions.Description: Index for each day in the specified date range. Index for the first day (i.e., start-date) in the date range is 0, 1 for the second day, and so on.

Dimensions.Name: Day of the month
Dimensions.Description: The day of the month. A two-digit number from 01 to 31.

Dimensions.Name: Day of Week
Dimensions.Description: The day of the week. A one-digit number from 0 (Sunday) to 6 (Saturday).

Dimensions.Name: Day of Week Name
Dimensions.Description: The name of the day of the week (in English).

Dimensions.Name: Days Since Last Session
Dimensions.Description: The number of days elapsed since users last visited your property. Used to calculate user loyalty.

Dimensions.Name: Days to Transaction
Dimensions.Description: The number of days between users' purchases and the related campaigns that lead to the purchases.

Dimensions.Name: Default Channel Grouping
Dimensions.Description: The default channel grouping that is shared within the View (Profile).

Dimensions.Name: Destination Page
Dimensions.Description: A page that the user visited after performing an internal search on your property.

Dimensions.Name: Destination URL
Dimensions.Description: The URLs to which your AdWords ads referred traffic.

Dimensions.Name: Device Category
Dimensions.Description: The type of device: desktop, tablet, or mobile.

Dimensions.Name: Display Name
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the title of the social activity posted by the social network user.

Dimensions.Name: Display URL
Dimensions.Description: The URLs your AdWords ads displayed.

Dimensions.Name: Endorsing URL
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the URL of the social activity (e.g. the Google+ post URL, the blog comment URL, etc.)

Dimensions.Name: Event Action
Dimensions.Description: The action of the event.

Dimensions.Name: Event Category
Dimensions.Description: The category of the event.

Dimensions.Name: Event Label
Dimensions.Description: The label of the event.

Dimensions.Name: Exception Description
Dimensions.Description: The description for the exception.

Dimensions.Name: Exit Page
Dimensions.Description: The last page in a user's session, or exit page.

Dimensions.Name: Exit Screen
Dimensions.Description: The name of the screen when the user exited the application.

Dimensions.Name: Experiment ID
Dimensions.Description: The user-scoped id of the content experiment that the user was exposed to when the metrics were reported.

Dimensions.Name: Flash Version
Dimensions.Description: The versions of Flash supported by users' browsers, including minor versions.

Dimensions.Name: Full Referrer
Dimensions.Description: The full referring URL including the hostname and path.

Dimensions.Name: Gender
Dimensions.Description: Gender of user.

Dimensions.Name: Goal Completion Location
Dimensions.Description: The page path or screen name that matched any destination type goal completion.

Dimensions.Name: Goal Previous Step - 1
Dimensions.Description: The page path or screen name that matched any destination type goal, one step prior to the goal completion location.

Dimensions.Name: Goal Previous Step - 2
Dimensions.Description: The page path or screen name that matched any destination type goal, two steps prior to the goal completion location.

Dimensions.Name: Goal Previous Step - 3
Dimensions.Description: The page path or screen name that matched any destination type goal, three steps prior to the goal completion location.

Dimensions.Name: Hostname
Dimensions.Description: The hostname from which the tracking request was made.

Dimensions.Name: Hour
Dimensions.Description: A two-digit hour of the day ranging from 00-23 in the timezone configured for the account. This value is also corrected for daylight savings time, adhering to all local rules for daylight savings time. If your timezone follows daylight savings time, there will be an apparent bump in the number of sessions during the change-over hour (e.g. between 1:00 and 2:00) for the day per year when that hour repeats. A corresponding hour with zero sessions will occur at the opposite changeover. (Google Analytics does not track user time more precisely than hours.)

Dimensions.Name: Hour Index
Dimensions.Description: Index for each hour in the specified date range. Index for the first hour of first day (i.e., start-date) in the date range is 0, 1 for the next hour, and so on.

Dimensions.Name: Hour of Day
Dimensions.Description: Combined values of ga:date and ga:hour.

Dimensions.Name: In-Market Segment
Dimensions.Description: Indicates that users are more likely to be ready to purchase products or services in the specified category.

Dimensions.Name: Internal Promotion Creative
Dimensions.Description: The creative content designed for a promotion (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Internal Promotion ID
Dimensions.Description: The ID of the promotion (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Internal Promotion Name
Dimensions.Description: The name of the promotion (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Internal Promotion Position
Dimensions.Description: The position of the promotion on the web page or application screen (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: ISO Week of ISO Year
Dimensions.Description: Combined values of ga:isoYear and ga:isoWeek.

Dimensions.Name: ISO Week of the Year
Dimensions.Description: The ISO week number, where each week starts with a Monday. Details: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_week_date. ga:isoWeek should only be used with ga:isoYear since ga:year represents gregorian calendar.

Dimensions.Name: ISO Year
Dimensions.Description: The ISO year of the session. Details: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_week_date. ga:isoYear should only be used with ga:isoWeek since ga:week represents gregorian calendar.

Dimensions.Name: Java Support
Dimensions.Description: Indicates Java support for users' browsers. The possible values are Yes or No where the first letter must be capitalized.

Dimensions.Name: Keyword
Dimensions.Description: When using manual campaign tracking, the value of the utm_term campaign tracking parameter. When using AdWords autotagging or if a user used organic search to reach your property, the keywords used by users to reach your property. Otherwise the value is (not set).

Dimensions.Name: Keyword Match Type
Dimensions.Description: The match types applied to your keywords (Phrase, Exact, Broad). Details: https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/2472708?hl=en

Dimensions.Name: Landing Page
Dimensions.Description: The first page in a user's session, or landing page.

Dimensions.Name: Landing Page Group XX
Dimensions.Description: The first matching content group in a user's session.

Dimensions.Name: Landing Screen
Dimensions.Description: The name of the first screen viewed.

Dimensions.Name: Language
Dimensions.Description: The language provided by the HTTP Request for the browser. Values are given as an ISO-639 code (e.g. en-gb for British English).

Dimensions.Name: Latitude
Dimensions.Description: The approximate latitude of the user's city. Derived from IP address. Locations north of the equator are represented by positive values and locations south of the equator by negative values.

Dimensions.Name: Longitude
Dimensions.Description: The approximate longitude of the user's city. Derived from IP address. Locations east of the meridian are represented by positive values and locations west of the meridian by negative values.

Dimensions.Name: Matched Search Query
Dimensions.Description: The search queries that triggered impressions of your AdWords ads.

Dimensions.Name: Medium
Dimensions.Description: The type of referrals to your property. When using manual campaign tracking, the value of the utm_medium campaign tracking parameter. When using AdWords autotagging, the value is ppc. If the user comes from a search engine detected by Google Analytics, the value is organic. If the referrer is not a search engine, the value is referral. If the users came directly to the property, and document.referrer is empty, the value is (none).

Dimensions.Name: Metro
Dimensions.Description: The Designated Market Area (DMA) from where traffic arrived on your property.

Dimensions.Name: Minute
Dimensions.Description: Returns the minute in the hour. The possible values are between 00 and 59.

Dimensions.Name: Minute Index
Dimensions.Description: Index for each minute in the specified date range. Index for the first minute of first day (i.e., start-date) in the date range is 0, 1 for the next minute, and so on.

Dimensions.Name: Mobile (Including Tablet)
Dimensions.Description: This dimension is deprecated and will be removed soon. Please use ga:deviceCategory instead (e.g., ga:deviceCategory==mobile).

Dimensions.Name: Mobile Device Branding
Dimensions.Description: Mobile manufacturer or branded name.

Dimensions.Name: Mobile Device Info
Dimensions.Description: The branding, model, and marketing name used to identify the mobile device.

Dimensions.Name: Mobile Device Marketing Name
Dimensions.Description: The marketing name used for the mobile device.

Dimensions.Name: Mobile Device Model
Dimensions.Description: Mobile device model

Dimensions.Name: Mobile Input Selector
Dimensions.Description: Selector used on the mobile device (e.g.: touchscreen, joystick, clickwheel, stylus).

Dimensions.Name: Month Index
Dimensions.Description: Index for each month in the specified date range. Index for the first month in the date range is 0, 1 for the second month, and so on. The index corresponds to month entries.

Dimensions.Name: Month of the year
Dimensions.Description: The month of the session. A two digit integer from 01 to 12.

Dimensions.Name: Month of Year
Dimensions.Description: Combined values of ga:year and ga:month.

Dimensions.Name: Network Domain
Dimensions.Description: The domain name of the ISPs used by users to your property. This is derived from the domain name registered to the IP address.

Dimensions.Name: Next Page Group XX
Dimensions.Description: Refers to content group that was visited after another content group.

Dimensions.Name: Next Page Path
Dimensions.Description: A page on your website that was visited after another page on your website. Typically used with the previousPagePath dimension.

Dimensions.Name: Operating System
Dimensions.Description: The operating system used by your users. For example, Windows, Linux , Macintosh, iPhone, iPod.

Dimensions.Name: Operating System Version
Dimensions.Description: The version of the operating system used by your users, such as XP for Windows or PPC for Macintosh.

Dimensions.Name: Order Coupon Code
Dimensions.Description: Code for the order-level coupon (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Originating Social Action
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the type of social action associated with the activity (e.g. vote, comment, +1, etc.).

Dimensions.Name: Other Category
Dimensions.Description: Indicates that users are more likely to be interested in learning about the specified category, and more likely to be ready to purchase.

Dimensions.Name: Page
Dimensions.Description: A page on your website specified by path and/or query parameters. Use in conjunction with hostname to get the full URL of the page.

Dimensions.Name: Page Depth
Dimensions.Description: The number of pages visited by users during a session. The value is a histogram that counts pageviews across a range of possible values. In this calculation, all sessions will have at least one pageview, and some percentage of sessions will have more.

Dimensions.Name: Page Group XX
Dimensions.Description: Content group on a web property. A content group is a collection of content providing a logical structure that can be determined by tracking code or page title/url regex match, or predefined rules.

Dimensions.Name: Page path level 1
Dimensions.Description: This dimension rolls up all the page paths in the first hierarchical level in pagePath.

Dimensions.Name: Page path level 2
Dimensions.Description: This dimension rolls up all the page paths in the second hierarchical level in pagePath.

Dimensions.Name: Page path level 3
Dimensions.Description: This dimension rolls up all the page paths in the third hierarchical level in pagePath.

Dimensions.Name: Page path level 4
Dimensions.Description: This dimension rolls up all the page paths into hierarchical levels. Up to 4 pagePath levels maybe specified. All additional levels in the pagePath hierarchy are also rolled up in this dimension.

Dimensions.Name: Page Title
Dimensions.Description: The title of a page. Keep in mind that multiple pages might have the same page title.

Dimensions.Name: Placement Domain
Dimensions.Description: The domains where your ads on the content network were placed.

Dimensions.Name: Placement Type
Dimensions.Description: How you manage your ads on the content network. Values are Automatic placements or Managed placements.

Dimensions.Name: Placement URL
Dimensions.Description: The URLs where your ads on the content network were placed.

Dimensions.Name: Previous Page Group XX
Dimensions.Description: Refers to content group that was visited before another content group.

Dimensions.Name: Previous Page Path
Dimensions.Description: A page on your property that was visited before another page on the same property. Typically used with the pagePath dimension.

Dimensions.Name: Product
Dimensions.Description: The product name for purchased items as supplied by your ecommerce tracking application.

Dimensions.Name: Product Brand
Dimensions.Description: The brand name under which the product is sold (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Product Category
Dimensions.Description: Any product variations (size, color) for purchased items as supplied by your ecommerce application. Not compatible with Enhanced Ecommerce.

Dimensions.Name: Product Category (Enhanced Ecommerce)
Dimensions.Description: The hierarchical category in which the product is classified (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Product Category Level XX
Dimensions.Description: Level (1-5) in the product category hierarchy, starting from the top (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Product Coupon Code
Dimensions.Description: Code for the product-level coupon (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Product List Name
Dimensions.Description: The name of the product list in which the product appears (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Product List Position
Dimensions.Description: The position of the product in the product list (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Product SKU
Dimensions.Description: The product sku for purchased items as you have defined them in your ecommerce tracking application.

Dimensions.Name: Product Variant
Dimensions.Description: The specific variation of a product, e.g., XS, S, M, L for size or Red, Blue, Green, Black for color (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Queried Product ID
Dimensions.Description: ID of the product being queried.

Dimensions.Name: Queried Product Name
Dimensions.Description: Name of the product being queried.

Dimensions.Name: Queried Product Variation
Dimensions.Description: Variation of the product being queried.

Dimensions.Name: Query Match Type
Dimensions.Description: The match types applied for the search term the user had input(Phrase, Exact, Broad, etc.). Ads on the content network are identified as "Content network". Details: https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/2472708?hl=en

Dimensions.Name: Referral Path
Dimensions.Description: The path of the referring URL (e.g. document.referrer). If someone places a link to your property on their website, this element contains the path of the page that contains the referring link.

Dimensions.Name: Refined Keyword
Dimensions.Description: Subsequent keyword search terms or strings entered by users after a given initial string search.

Dimensions.Name: Region
Dimensions.Description: The region of users to your property, derived from IP addresses. In the U.S., a region is a state, such as New York.

Dimensions.Name: Related Product ID
Dimensions.Description: ID of the related product.

Dimensions.Name: Related Product Name
Dimensions.Description: Name of the related product.

Dimensions.Name: Related Product Variation
Dimensions.Description: Variation of the related product.

Dimensions.Name: Screen Colors
Dimensions.Description: The color depth of users' monitors, as retrieved from the DOM of the user's browser. For example 4-bit, 8-bit, 24-bit, or undefined-bit.

Dimensions.Name: Screen Depth
Dimensions.Description: The number of screenviews per session reported as a string. Can be useful for historgrams.

Dimensions.Name: Screen Name
Dimensions.Description: The name of the screen.

Dimensions.Name: Screen Resolution
Dimensions.Description: The screen resolution of users' screens. For example: 1024x738.

Dimensions.Name: Search Term
Dimensions.Description: Search terms used by users within your property.

Dimensions.Name: Second Page
Dimensions.Description: The second page in a user's session.

Dimensions.Name: Service Provider
Dimensions.Description: The name of service providers used to reach your property. For example, if most users to your website come via the major service providers for cable internet, you will see the names of those cable service providers in this element.

Dimensions.Name: Session Duration
Dimensions.Description: The length of a session on your property measured in seconds and reported in second increments. The value returned is a string.

Dimensions.Name: Sessions to Transaction
Dimensions.Description: The number of sessions between users' purchases and the related campaigns that lead to the purchases.

Dimensions.Name: Shared URL
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the URL shared by the associated social network user.

Dimensions.Name: Shopping Stage
Dimensions.Description: Various stages of the shopping experience that users completed in a session, e.g., PRODUCT_VIEW, ADD_TO_CART, CHECKOUT, etc. (Enhanced Ecommerce).

Dimensions.Name: Site Search Category
Dimensions.Description: The categories used for the internal search if you have this enabled for your profile. For example, you might have product categories such as electronics, furniture, or clothing.

Dimensions.Name: Site Search Status
Dimensions.Description: A boolean to distinguish whether internal search was used in a session. Values are Visits With Site Search and Visits Without Site Search.

Dimensions.Name: Social Action
Dimensions.Description: For social interactions, a value representing the social action being tracked (e.g. +1, bookmark)

Dimensions.Name: Social Activity Post
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the content of the social activity posted by the social network user (e.g. The message content of a Google+ post)

Dimensions.Name: Social Activity Timestamp
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents when the social activity occurred on the social network.

Dimensions.Name: Social Entity
Dimensions.Description: For social interactions, a value representing the URL (or resource) which receives the social network action.

Dimensions.Name: Social Network
Dimensions.Description: Name of the social network. This can be related to the referring social network for traffic sources, or to the social network for social data hub activities. E.g. Google+, Blogger, etc.

Dimensions.Name: Social Network and Action
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the type of social action and the social network where the activity originated.

Dimensions.Name: Social Source
Dimensions.Description: For social interactions, a value representing the social network being tracked.

Dimensions.Name: Social Source and Action
Dimensions.Description: For social interactions, a value representing the concatenation of the socialInteractionNetwork and socialInteractionAction action being tracked at this hit level (e.g. Google: +1)

Dimensions.Name: Social Source Referral
Dimensions.Description: Indicates sessions that arrived to the property from a social source. The possible values are Yes or No where the first letter is capitalized.

Dimensions.Name: Social Tags Summary
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this is a comma-separated set of tags associated with the social activity.

Dimensions.Name: Social Type
Dimensions.Description: Engagement type. Possible values are "Socially Engaged" or "Not Socially Engaged".

Dimensions.Name: Social User Handle
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the social network handle (e.g. name or ID) of the user who initiated the social activity.

Dimensions.Name: Source
Dimensions.Description: The source of referrals to your property. When using manual campaign tracking, the value of the utm_source campaign tracking parameter. When using AdWords autotagging, the value is google. Otherwise the domain of the source referring the user to your property (e.g. document.referrer). The value may also contain a port address. If the user arrived without a referrer, the value is (direct)

Dimensions.Name: Source / Medium
Dimensions.Description: Combined values of ga:source and ga:medium.

Dimensions.Name: Source Property Display Name
Dimensions.Description: Source property display name of roll-up properties. This is valid only for roll-up properties.

Dimensions.Name: Source Property Tracking ID
Dimensions.Description: Source property tracking ID of roll-up properties. This is valid only for roll-up properties.

Dimensions.Name: Start Page
Dimensions.Description: A page where the user initiated an internal search on your property.

Dimensions.Name: Sub Continent Region
Dimensions.Description: The sub-continent of users, derived from IP addresses. For example, Polynesia or Northern Europe.

Dimensions.Name: Tablet
Dimensions.Description: This dimension is deprecated and will be removed soon. Please use ga:deviceCategory instead (e.g., ga:deviceCategory==tablet).

Dimensions.Name: Targeting Type
Dimensions.Description: How your AdWords ads were targeted (keyword, placement, and vertical targeting, etc.).

Dimensions.Name: Timing Category
Dimensions.Description: A string for categorizing all user timing variables into logical groups for easier reporting purposes.

Dimensions.Name: Timing Label
Dimensions.Description: The name of the resource's action being tracked.

Dimensions.Name: Timing Variable
Dimensions.Description: A value that can be used to add flexibility in visualizing user timings in the reports.

Dimensions.Name: Transaction ID
Dimensions.Description: The transaction ID for the shopping cart purchase as supplied by your ecommerce tracking method.

Dimensions.Name: TrueView Video Ad
Dimensions.Description: 'Yes' or 'No' - Indicates whether the ad is an AdWords TrueView video ad.

Dimensions.Name: User Defined Value
Dimensions.Description: The value provided when you define custom user segments for your property.

Dimensions.Name: User Photo URL
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the URL of the photo associated with the user's social network profile.

Dimensions.Name: User Profile URL
Dimensions.Description: For a social data hub activity, this value represents the URL of the associated user's social network profile.

Dimensions.Name: User Type
Dimensions.Description: A boolean indicating if a user is new or returning. Possible values: New Visitor, Returning Visitor.

Dimensions.Name: Variation
Dimensions.Description: The user-scoped id of the particular variation that the user was exposed to during a content experiment.

Dimensions.Name: Week Index
Dimensions.Description: Index for each week in the specified date range. Index for the first week in the date range is 0, 1 for the second week, and so on. The index corresponds to week entries.

Dimensions.Name: Week of the Year
Dimensions.Description: The week of the session. A two-digit number from 01 to 53. Each week starts on Sunday.

Dimensions.Name: Week of Year
Dimensions.Description: Combined values of ga:year and ga:week.

Dimensions.Name: Year
Dimensions.Description: The year of the session. A four-digit year from 2005 to the current year.

Dimensions.Name: Session Count
Dimensions.Description: The visit index for a visitor to your website. Each visit from a unique visitor will get its own incremental index starting from 1 for the first visit. Subsequent visits do not change previous visit indicies. For example, if a certain visitor has 4 visits to your website, ga:visitCount for that visitor will have 4 distinct values of '1' through '4'.
